@page "/contact"

<!-- ========================= -->
<!-- HERO (dark green) -->
<!-- ========================= -->
<section class="hero">
    <div class="section-inner">
        <h1>Contact Ripple (Conceptual)</h1>
        <p>
            Ripple is a proof‑of‑concept project created for a college honors program. 
            While there is no active organization to contact, this page demonstrates 
            how a real nonprofit might provide communication channels for volunteers, 
            partners, and community members.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<div class="divider-coral"></div>

<!-- ========================= -->
<!-- MODELED CONTACT INFO (pale coral) -->
<!-- ========================= -->
<section class="pale-coral">
    <div class="section-inner">
        <h2>Modeled Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
            In a real implementation, this page would include:
        </p>

        <ul class="icon-list">
            <li><i class="fa-solid fa-envelope"></i> A general inquiry email address</li>
            <li><i class="fa-solid fa-handshake-angle"></i> A volunteer or partnership form</li>
            <li><i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot"></i> Location and facility tour information</li>
            <li><i class="fa-solid fa-clock"></i> Office hours or response expectations</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            For this project, these elements are placeholders used to illustrate 
            how communication would work in a real nonprofit setting.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
